text: John Hercules Duus (1906-1991) was an athlete who competed for England. ==Athletics career== Duus competed in the javelin at the 1934 British Empire Games in London and was part of the Manchester Athletic Club. ==References== Category:1906 births Category:1991 deaths Category:English male javelin throwers Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1934 British Empire Games
title: John Duus
